    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Check engine oil pressure"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. Remove engine oil pressure switch",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000399",
          "label": "Remove engine oil pressure switch",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "2. Oil Pressure Gauge Installation"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "400_3.0_jpn_11034343_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Install oil pressure gauge attachment PT/1/8 (07406-0030000) and oil pressure gauge set (07506-3000001)."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "3. Engine Warming up"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Start the engine and allow the engine to warm up until the radiator fan operates twice."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "4. Engine oil pressure Check"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "After warm-up is complete, measure oil pressure and if oil pressure is low, perform the following inspections. Oil pressure (after completion of warm-up) When idling: 1 70kPa(0.71kgf/cm 2 ) or more At 3,000 rpm: 1,000 rpm 230kPa(2.35kgf/cm 2 ) or more After measurement, remove the oil pressure gauge set and the oil pressure gauge attachment PT/1/8.",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000407",
          "label": "Inspect oil pump relief valve.",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        {
          "text": "Oil filter clogged"
        },
        {
          "text": "Oil filter clogged"
        },
        {
          "text": "Oil strainer clogged"
        },
        {
